com.movo.wave

Class WaveAgent.BLERequestWaveOp

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.movo.wave.BLEAgent.BLERequest
      • com.movo.wave.WaveAgent.BLERequestWaveOp
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    WaveAgent.WaveRequestClearData, WaveAgent.WaveRequestDataByDay, WaveAgent.WaveRequestGetDate, WaveAgent.WaveRequestReadDeviceData, WaveAgent.WaveRequestResetDevice, WaveAgent.WaveRequestSetDate, WaveAgent.WaveRequestSetName, WaveAgent.WaveRequestSetPersonalInfo
    Enclosing class:
    WaveAgent

    public abstract static class WaveAgent.BLERequestWaveOp
extends BLEAgent.BLERequest
    Abstract base class for interacting with wave device using WaveOp and byte[] buffers. Concisely, the class implements the pattern: Writes an op, receives notify. Recommended strategy to prevent code bloat: subclass for each op, and add appropriate abstract onComplete(...) methods for return data types, using byte[] onComplete as a parser.

        public boolean onReceive(android.bluetooth.BluetoothGattCharacteristic characteristic,
                         int status)
        De-multiplex write and notify characteristics, warn if other characteristic observed. Switch on characteristic UUID: - on write failure abort - on notify, checksum and verify op status, forward to onComplete( with value ).
        Overrides:

        Parameters:

        status - status associated with the gatt event.
        Returns:
